# Kotlin and project core

## Language and style

- Use Kotlin only.
- Prefer immutable data (`val`, immutable models).
- Keep functions small and single-purpose; use explicit names (avoid abbreviations).
- Avoid duplication; prefer reusable components when the same UI or logic repeats.

## User-visible text

- Use string resources, not literals in code; when you add or change default strings, update every shipped locale under `res/values*` (details in the string-resources rule when editing those files).

## Architecture (all layers)

- MVVM with unidirectional flow: UI → ViewModel → UseCase (when present) → Repository.
- Domain logic must not depend on the Android framework.
- The UI layer must not access repositories directly.

## Working in this codebase

- Preserve existing architecture unless the user asks to change it.
- Prefer refactoring over rewriting.
- Do not add new libraries without a clear justification.
- Follow existing naming, module layout, and patterns in nearby code.
- Do not run Gradle builds (`./gradlew`, `gradlew.bat`, assemble, compile tasks, etc.) after edits unless the user explicitly asks to build or verify the build.
